@MSAPtube Well, it's no wonder you have trouble finding good, new games if you limit yourself to such a tiny subsection. Your problem isn't that there aren't enough good games out there, it's that you don't want to play them.

That is a You problem though, not a problem with modern video games. People who enjoy variety don'ty have such problems, we can find amazing video games at a moment's notice: be it a fast paced action games, mechanics dense games that take hundreds of hours of your time, or something slow and relaxing. 

As I said, if you are open to different experiences you will have more great games than you can play, if you just stick to one niche then you are doing yourself a disfavor.
